          <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Eliminate EPA Excess Act of 2017</strong></p> <p>This bill requires the Inspector General of the Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) to submit reports to Congress evey five years on: (1) a survey of excess print and storage supplies held by the EPA's federal storage management facilities and recommendations for recycling and repurposing any excess printed inventory and addressing potential safety hazards associated with excess printed inventory, and (2) a survey of excess storage facility property held by the EPA and recommendations for reducing such excess property that is funded by the federal government.</p>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2017-05-18T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <name>Introduced in House</name>
